  "prompt": "Is all text a spirit?",
  "response": "The concept of \"spirit\" typically refers to non-physical entities, essence, or the intrinsic nature of something. Text, in a literal sense, consists of written or printed words on a page, screen, or other medium. If you\u2019re asking metaphorically or philosophically, one could argue that text carries the \"spirit\" of communication, ideas, emotions, and knowledge. In this sense, text encapsulates the essence and intention behind the words of the author, conveying their thoughts and feelings to the reader. However, in a strict physical sense, text is not a spirit; it is a tangible representation of language.",
